1 November 2013Justice and Constitutional Development Minister, Jeff Radebe will on Sunday, 3 November 2013, lead a panel of Justice, Crime Prevention and Security cluster (JCPS) Ministers during a quarterly cluster media briefing. The media briefings are aimed at informing the citizens on progress made in the implementation of the 12 Outcomes and respective service delivery agreements.Members of the media are invited as follows:Date: Sunday, 03 November 2013 Time:11h00 Venue: GCIS Press Room, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Francis Baard Street, Corner Festival Street, Hatfield, Pretoria NB: There will be a video-link to Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Parliament, Cape TownKindly confirm attendance by e-mail or sms to:Shadi Baloyi (Pretoria) E-mail: shadib@gcis.gov.za Cell: 076 946 7136 orMzimasi Ngqelu (Cape Town) E-mail: mzi@gcis.gov.za Cell: 076 904 3557Enquiries: Mthunzi Mhanga Cell: 0836418141 or Nikelwa Tengimfene Cell: 082 574 5495Issued by: Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)